<p class=""><h2>Key Challenges in the Potato Granules Market</h2><ul>    <li><strong>Raw Material Supply:</strong> The availability and price volatility of raw potatoes pose significant challenges. Fluctuations due to weather conditions, transportation issues, and agricultural productivity can affect the overall production cost.</li>    <li><strong>Quality Control:</strong> Maintaining consistent quality in potato granules is crucial. Variations in potato quality can lead to differences in texture, flavor, and nutritional value, impacting consumer satisfaction.</li>    <li><strong>Competition from Substitutes:</strong> The food industry is witnessing a rise in alternative ingredients, such as rice or tapioca-based products. This significant competition can limit market growth for potato-based offerings.</li>    <li><strong>Health Trends:</strong> Rising health awareness and dietary shifts toward low-carb and gluten-free options can negatively impact the demand for potato-based products, as consumers may lean towards perceived healthier alternatives.</li>    <li><strong>Technological Advancements:</strong> The need for continuous innovation to improve processing efficiency and product quality can strain small and medium enterprises. These companies may lack the resources to invest in advanced technologies.</li>    <li><strong>Market Penetration:</strong> Expanding into new markets and reaching diverse consumer demographics remain challenging. Limited awareness and established preferences for staple foods can hinder growth.</li></ul><h2>Potential Growth Opportunities in the Potato Granules Market</h2><ul>    <li><strong>Innovation in Product Development:</strong> There is a growing opportunity for product innovations such as flavored or fortified potato granules, catering to health-conscious consumers and expanding food applications like snacks and ready-to-eat meals.</li>    <li><strong>Expanding Food Applications:</strong> The versatility of potato granules in vario